description.narrative: Since 2008 Oxfam Novib’s WEMAN programme has been supporting the development of an innovative Gender Action Learning System (GALS), a community-led empowerment methodology to facilitate the integration of gender issues into livelihood approaches and rural value chain development. The aim was to develop an participatory approach that combines the business sense of gender equality with the human rights case. And equally important: to show that gender equality is grounded in the realities and demands of women and men in vulnerable communities, and cannot be dismissed as an imposition from donors and feminist organisations in the West.

participating-org.narrative: Youth in Difficult Circumstances is a project implemented in 3 countries: Pakistan, Zimbabwe and South Africa. It is funded by the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs for the period of 2014-2017 and managed by Oxfam Novib The Hague
